          <msContents>
            <summary>Manuscript is used for contemplation, study, and recitation and is a post-Vedic Hindu philosophical treatise that has been influenced by both saṃkhyā and Vedānta schools of philosophy, synthesizing traditions associated with yoga and other contemplative practices in formulating a connection between an understanding of ultimate reality and the individual self (ātman). Manuscript is part of a larger group of late upaniṣads known as the Yoga-upaniṣads.</summary>
            <textLang mainLang="san">In Sanskrit</textLang>
